# Acvilas Medical Management Software — User Manual

---

## Chapter 1: Home / Dashboard

The **Dashboard** is the first screen you see when you log in to Acvilas. It gives you a complete real-time overview of your clinic's daily activity.

---

### 1.1 Accessing the Dashboard

When you open Acvilas, you will be automatically directed to the **Home** screen. You can also return to it at any time by clicking **Home** in the left-side navigation menu (highlighted in purple when active).

---

### 1.2 Top Navigation Bar (Appointment Filter)

At the top right of the Dashboard, you will find the **All Appointment** filter panel. This allows you to:

- **Filter by Doctor** — By default it shows "All doctors selected." Click this to filter statistics for a specific doctor.
- **Filter by Date** — The date selector shows the current month (e.g., *April 2026*). Click the calendar icon to change the date range and view historical data.

---

### 1.3 Appointment Summary Cards

Just below the top bar, you will see **8 summary stat cards** that give you a quick count of all appointments for the selected period:

| Card | Color | What It Shows |
|---|---|---|
| **Total** | Grey | Total number of appointments |
| **Pending** | Orange | Appointments not yet actioned |
| **Attended** | Blue | Patients who have arrived |
| **Cancelled** | Red | Appointments that were cancelled |
| **Completed** | Green | Fully completed appointments |
| **Waiting** | Yellow | Patients currently waiting |
| **Revisit** | Purple | Patients scheduled for a follow-up |
| **Refunds** | Orange-Red | Refund transactions processed |

> **Tip:** These numbers update in real time. Click the **Refresh** link next to the Dashboard title to manually refresh the data.

---

### 1.4 Appointment Volume Chart

The left chart on the Dashboard displays **Appointment Volume** over the current month (Days 1–19 in the example).

- The **X-axis** represents the days of the month.
- The **Y-axis** represents the number of appointments.
- Each **colored line** represents a different appointment status:

| Color | Status |
|---|---|
| 🟡 Yellow | Pending |
| 🔵 Blue | Patient Attended |
| 🔴 Red | Cancelled |
| 🟢 Green | Completed |
| ⚫ Black | Waiting |
| 🟣 Purple | Revisit |
| 🟠 Orange | Pay Return |
| 🩷 Pink | Total |

Use this chart to **identify busy days**, spot trends, and manage staff scheduling.

---

### 1.5 Financial Stream Chart

The right chart displays the **Financial Stream** — income activity over the same date range.

- **APD** (shown in Yellow) — Appointment/service revenue
- **PROD** (shown in Blue) — Product/pharmacy sales revenue

Use this chart to monitor **daily revenue trends** and identify high-income days.

---

### 1.6 Left Side Navigation Menu

The vertical menu on the left provides access to all modules of the software:

| Menu Item | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Home** | Returns to this Dashboard |
| **OPD** | Outpatient Department management |
| **Appointment** | Create and view appointments |
| **App. Management** | Manage appointment settings |
| **Customers** | Patient/customer records |
| **Time Table** | Doctor schedules and availability |
| **Cashier** | Payment and billing counter |
| **Service Task** | Clinical service task tracking |
| **Invoice** | Generate and manage invoices |
| **TV Projector** | Display queue/info on waiting room screen |
| **Reports** | Generate operational and financial reports |
| **Administration** | System settings and user management |

> The menu can be **collapsed** by clicking the small arrow (◀) at the top right of the sidebar to give more screen space.

---

### 1.7 User Profile (Bottom Left)

At the bottom of the left menu, you will see the **logged-in user's profile**, displaying:

- Profile photo
- Username (e.g., *ADMIN*)
- Role (e.g., *ADMINISTRATOR*)

Click on this area to access profile settings or log out.

---

# Chapter 2: OPD (Outpatient Department)

The **OPD module** is the core clinical workspace in Acvilas. It is where doctors see patients, record prescriptions, add services, dispense products, and complete consultations. Navigate to it by clicking **OPD** in the left sidebar.

---

## 2.1 OPD Screen Overview

At the top of the OPD screen you will see:

| Element | Description |
|---|---|
| **Doctor Name & Tagline** | Shows the active doctor (e.g., *Test Doctor*) |
| **Token No** | Displays the current patient token number. Use the **◀ ▶ arrows** to navigate between tokens |
| **Token Print** | Prints a physical token slip for the patient |
| **Session 1** | Indicates the current active session. Click to switch sessions if multiple are configured |
| **Today List** | Opens the full list of today's patients (see Section 2.6) |
| **Patient History** | Appears once a patient is loaded — shows the patient's past visit records |
| **Save** | Saves the current consultation record (orange button) |
| **Complete** | Marks the consultation as fully completed (green button) |

---

## 2.2 Finding / Loading a Patient

On the **right panel** under **Customer Information**, you can locate an existing patient using three methods:

### Option A — Search by Phone
1. Select the **Phone** radio button.
2. Type the patient's phone number in the search field.
3. The system will display matching patient records below.
4. Click the correct patient name to load their record.

### Option B — Search by User ID
1. Select the **User ID** radio button.
2. Type the patient's User ID (F2 shortcut to focus the field).
3. Select the matching record from the results list.

### Option C — ID Scan
1. Click the **ID Scan** button.
2. Scan the patient's ID using a connected scanner or camera.
3. The system will auto-fill and load the patient record.

> **Keyboard Shortcut:** Press **F2** to quickly jump to the User ID search field.

---

## 2.3 Adding a New Patient

If the patient does not exist in the system:

1. Click the **Add New** button (purple, top right of Customer Information panel).
2. Fill in the patient details in the form that appears.
3. Alternatively, click **Create New Record** (green button) that appears in the search results area after a failed search.
4. Enter optional fields such as **Age** and **City** in the Customer Data section.

> **Keyboard Shortcut:** Press **F8** or click **EMPTY CUSTOMER ENTRY (F8)** to quickly clear all fields and start a fresh patient entry.

---

## 2.4 Acvilas AI — Specialised Intelligence Panel

Once a patient is loaded, the **Acvilas AI** panel appears automatically in the main workspace area. This is an AI-powered clinical assistant built into the software.

### What it does:
- Automatically generates a **clinical summary** of the patient including chronic conditions, surgical history, allergies, current medications, and social history.
- Displays the summary across multiple pages (e.g., *1 / 6* — use the **◀ ▶** arrows to navigate pages).

### How to use it:
- Read the auto-generated summary at the top of the panel.
- Use the **"Ask about patient history…"** text box at the bottom to type a specific clinical question about the patient and press **Ask**.
- The AI will respond based on the patient's stored records.

> ⚠️ **Important Notice:** *Acvilas AI is not a real doctor — it is a helpful assistant only.* Always apply clinical judgment.

---

## 2.5 Consultation Record — Prescription Tab

Once a patient is selected and a token is assigned (Token No changes from 0 to 1, 2, etc.), the main consultation form becomes active. The default tab is **Prescription**.

### Clinical Fields:

| Field | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Past Medical History** | Enter the patient's known medical background |
| **Presenting Complaint** | Enter the reason for today's visit |
| **Allergies** | Record any known drug or other allergies |
| **Treatments** | Note the treatment plan decided by the doctor |

### Outside Prescription (Drug Entry):

Use the table at the bottom of the Prescription tab to add medications:

| Column | What to Enter |
|---|---|
| **Drug Name** | Type the name of the medication |
| **Qty** | Enter the quantity to dispense |
| **Dosage** | Select or type the dose amount |
| **Frequency** | How often to take (e.g., twice daily) |
| **Days** | Number of days for the course |

After filling in each row, click the green **Add** button to add it to the prescription list.

### Other Prescription Tools:
- **Attachments** — Upload files from your computer (documents, lab results, images, photos, PDFs, etc.) to attach to this consultation record.
- **Print** — Print the prescription directly.
- **Make Template** — Save the current item list as a reusable template for future consultations.
- **Clear All Items** — Remove all added items from the current record.

---

## 2.6 Services Tab

Click the **Services** tab to add billable clinical services to the patient's visit.

- Use the **Search by Name, Title or Code** field to find a specific service.
- Filter services by responsible staff using the **All Doctors & Paramedicals** dropdown.

The services list shows:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Service Name** | The category of the service |
| **Title** | The specific service title |
| **CODE** | The service billing code |
| **Responsible** | Who performs the service (doctor/none) |
| **Res. Name** | The assigned staff member's name |
| **Task** | Whether a service task is created — **Yes** (green) or **No** (red) |
| **Total Price** | The charge for the service |
| **Option** | Click **Add** to attach the service to the patient's bill |

---

## 2.7 Templates Tab

Click **Templates** to load a previously saved consultation template. This is useful for common or recurring visit types (e.g., a standard consultation package), saving data entry time.

---

## 2.8 Products Tab

Click the **Products** tab to dispense pharmacy or clinic products directly from the OPD screen.

- Use the **(F9) Search by Generic, Code, or Name** field to quickly find a product.
- Click **Refresh** to reload the latest stock list.

The product list shows:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Generic Name** | The generic/chemical name of the product |
| **Code** | The stock/inventory code |
| **Name** | The brand name |
| **Unit Price** | The price per unit |
| **Quantity** | Current stock available (negative means stock adjustment needed) |
| **Option** | Click **Add** to add the product to the patient's bill |

---

## 2.9 Today List

Click the **Today List** button at the top of the OPD screen to open a popup showing all patients registered for the current day.

The list can be filtered using three tabs:

| Tab | Shows |
|---|---|
| **All** | Every patient registered today |
| **Pending** | Patients waiting to be seen |
| **In Progress** | Patients currently being consulted |
| **Complete** | Patients whose consultation is finished |

Each row in the list shows:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Token No** | The queue number assigned to the patient |
| **Record ID** | The system record ID |
| **Name** | Patient name |
| **Phone** | Patient contact number |
| **Status** | Current status (pending / in progress / complete) |
| **Load Record** | Click to open that patient's consultation in the OPD screen |
| **Remove** | Click to remove the patient from today's queue |

---

## 2.10 Attaching Files (Acvisync & Upload)

Within the Prescription tab, the **Attachments** button allows you to attach files to a patient's consultation record. Supported methods include:

- **Upload from Computer** — Click Attachments and browse your device to select and upload any file type (images, PDFs, lab reports, X-rays, documents, etc.).
- **Acvisync (Mobile Upload via QR Code)** — Acvilas supports a mobile sync option where you can scan a QR code on your phone to connect your mobile device and upload photos or files directly from your mobile camera or gallery into the patient's record wirelessly.

---

## 2.11 Completing a Consultation

Once all information has been entered:

1. Click **Save** (orange button) to save the record without closing it.
2. Click **Complete** (green button) to mark the consultation as done. This will move the patient's status to "Complete" in the Today List and update the Dashboard counters accordingly.

---
# Chapter 3: Appointment

The **Appointment** module allows staff to schedule, view, manage, and track patient appointments for all doctors. Access it by clicking **Appointment** in the left sidebar.

---

## 3.1 Appointment Screen Overview

The main Appointment screen contains the following key areas:

| Element | Description |
|---|---|
| **Refresh** | Reloads the appointment list with the latest data |
| **+ New Appointment** | Opens the form to create a new appointment |
| **Doctor's Register** | Opens the doctor attendance/register log |
| **Date Selector (top bar)** | A horizontal scrollable calendar — click any date to view appointments for that day. The current/selected date is highlighted in dark |
| **All Appointment / All doctors selected** | Filter panel — click to narrow results to a specific doctor |
| **Available Doctors and Appointment Charges** | Shows active doctors with their consultation charge (e.g., *Test Doctor | 2000.00*). Badge number shows count of appointments |
| **Search by Phone number** | Search field to quickly find a patient's appointment by phone |
| **Waiting List** | View patients currently on the waiting list |
| **Download CSV** | Export the current appointment list as a spreadsheet file |

---

## 3.2 Appointment Status Tabs

Below the search bar, appointments are filtered by status tabs:

| Tab | What It Shows |
|---|---|
| **All** | Every appointment for the selected date |
| **Pending** | Appointments not yet acted upon |
| **Online** | Appointments booked through an online channel |
| **Attend** | Patients who have arrived at the clinic |
| **Paid** | Appointments where payment has been received |
| **Complete** | Fully completed appointments |
| **Cancel** | Cancelled appointments |

---

## 3.3 Appointment List Columns

Each appointment row in the list displays:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **ID** | Unique appointment ID number |
| **Doctor** | The assigned doctor's name |
| **C. Name** | Customer (patient) name |
| **C. Phone** | Customer phone number |
| **Ap. Date** | Scheduled appointment date |
| **Ap. Time** | Scheduled appointment time |
| **Status** | Current status badge (e.g., Revisit, Pending, Complete) |
| **Note** | Any notes added to the appointment |
| **Create at** | Date and time the appointment was created |
| **Payment** | The consultation fee amount |
| **Paid** | Payment status — **Not Paid** (red) or **Paid** (green) |
| **Details** | Click **View** to open the full appointment details popup |

---

## 3.4 Viewing Appointment Details

Click **View** in the Details column to open the **Appointment Details** popup. This shows a full breakdown of the appointment:

### Appointment Data
- **Appointment ID** — Unique reference number
- **Created at** — Timestamp of when the appointment was created
- **Created user** — The staff member who created it

### Customer
- **Customer ID**, **Name**, and **Phone**

### Schedule
- **Date** — The appointment date
- **Time** — The appointment time

### Doctor
- **Name** — Assigned doctor
- **Title** — Doctor's specialisation (e.g., *Aesthetic Physician*)

### Billing
- **Payment** — The amount due (e.g., LKR 2000)
- **Payment Type** — Whether payment is collected *Before* or *After* the consultation
- **Bill ID** — Payment status badge (*Not Paid* / *Paid*)

### Status
- **Status** — Current appointment status (e.g., *revisit*)
- **Note** — Editable notes field. Click **Edit** to add or modify a note.
- **View Logs** — Click to see a full activity log for this appointment

### Action Buttons (bottom of popup)

| Button | Action |
|---|---|
| **Mark the patient as attend** (blue) | Marks the patient as arrived at the clinic |
| **Send to waiting list** (green) | Moves the patient to the waiting queue |
| **Change Date** (black) | Reschedules the appointment to a new date |
| **Cancel Appointment** (orange) | Cancels the appointment |

---

## 3.5 Creating a New Appointment

Click **+ New Appointment** (top right) to open the **New Appointment** form.

### Step 1 — Doctor & Queue Info
The form shows:
- The **assigned doctor** name and title (e.g., *Test Doctor — Aesthetic Physician*)
- The **Queue number** auto-assigned for the selected day
- The **Customer date** field auto-fills with today's date

### Step 2 — Select a Date
Use the **calendar on the left** to pick the appointment date. Click the **◀ ▶** arrows to navigate between months. The current date is circled in blue. Dates shown in red are Sundays or holidays.

### Step 3 — Select a Time Slot
The centre panel shows two tabs:
- **Default Time** — Pre-configured time slots set up in the doctor's schedule
- **Flex Schedule** — Flexible or custom time slots. If no schedule is configured, it will show *"No schedule found"*

Click on an available time slot to select it.

### Step 4 — Add a Note (Optional)
Click the **Note** dropdown at the top to add any remarks about the appointment.

### Step 5 — Select the Patient
On the right panel under **Customer Information**:
- Search by **Phone** or **User ID**
- Use **ID Scan** to scan the patient's ID
- Click **Add new** to register a new patient
- Press **F8** or click **EMPTY CUSTOMER ENTRY** to clear the form

### Step 6 — Confirm
Once a date, time, and patient are all selected, click **Make Appointment** (top right, activates when all fields are filled) to save the appointment.

---

## 3.6 Doctor's Register

Click **Doctor's Register** (blue button, top right of the Appointment screen) to open the doctor attendance register popup.

### Mark Register Tab
This tab is used to record a doctor's arrival for a specific day:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Date** | The date of the register entry |
| **Time** | The time the entry was recorded |
| **Status** | Attendance status — **Not Arrived** (red) or **Arrived** |
| **Room** | Enter the room number the doctor will be using |
| **Update** | Click to save the room number or update the record |
| **Send Notify SMS** | Sends an SMS notification to relevant parties about the doctor's status |

Use the **date picker** at the top right to view or mark the register for a specific date.

### All Register Tab
This tab shows a full historical attendance log for all doctors within a date range:

1. Set the **Start date** and **End date** using the date pickers.
2. Click **Load Data** to retrieve the records.

The results table shows:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Name** | Doctor's name |
| **Status** | Arrival status — **Not Arrived** (red) / **Arrived** (green) |
| **Date** | The date of the record |
| **Time** | Time recorded |
| **Room No** | Room assigned to the doctor |
| **Notify SMS** | Whether the notification SMS was sent — **Notify Not Sent** (red) or sent (green) |
| **Arrived SMS** | Whether the arrival SMS was sent — **Arrived SMS Not Sent** (red) or sent (green) |

> **Tip:** Use the All Register tab to audit doctor attendance and SMS notification history across any date range.

---

# Chapter 4: Appointment Management

The **Appointment Management** module is a dedicated workspace for managing the live patient queue and waiting list for a doctor's session. It bridges the gap between scheduled appointments and active consultations. Access it by clicking **App. Management** in the left sidebar.

---

## 4.1 Appointment Management Screen Overview

When you open the module, you will see:

| Element | Description |
|---|---|
| **Doctor Name & Title** | Displays the active doctor (e.g., *Test Doctor — Aesthetic Physician*) |
| **Token No** | Shows the current active token number. Use **◀ ▶** arrows to navigate between tokens |
| **Waiting List** | A panel showing patients currently in the waiting queue for this doctor |

When no patients are in the queue, the Waiting List area will be empty. Once patients are sent to the waiting list (from the Appointment module), they will appear here.

---

## 4.2 Waiting List Popup

Click on the **Waiting List** panel or header to open the **Waiting List popup** for the active doctor and today's date (e.g., *Waiting List | Test Doctor | 2026-04-19*).

The list is indexed by Appointment ID and shows:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Que** | The queue position number |
| **App. ID** | The appointment's unique ID |
| **C. Name** | The patient's name |
| **C. Phone** | The patient's phone number |
| **Status** | Current status badge — **Waiting** (blue) |
| **Mark Complete** | Click to mark this patient's appointment as completed without opening the full record |
| **Open** | Click to open the full consultation record for this patient |

> **Tip:** Use **Mark Complete** for quick administrative closures. Use **Open** when the doctor needs to record clinical notes, prescriptions, or services.

---

## 4.3 Opening a Patient Record from the Waiting List

Clicking **Open** on a waiting list entry loads the full consultation workspace within the Appointment Management screen. This is functionally identical to the OPD consultation view, and displays:

### Patient Header Bar
At the top of the screen, a summary header shows key appointment details at a glance:

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| **Patient Name** | The patient's full name (e.g., *Mr. Layan*) |
| **Customer Data** | Link to view or edit the patient's profile |
| **App ID** | The appointment reference ID |
| **Date Time** | Scheduled date and time of the appointment |
| **Bill ID** | Current billing/payment status (e.g., *Not paid*) |
| **Status** | Current status (e.g., *waiting*) |
| **Mark Complete** | Green button — click to mark the consultation as complete |
| **Save** | Orange button — saves the current record without completing |

### Token Navigation
The **Token No** at the top left updates to the current patient's token (e.g., Token 1). Use the **◀ ▶** arrows to move between patients in the queue.

---

## 4.4 Consultation Record

Once a patient is opened from the waiting list, the full consultation form becomes available. This includes the same tabs and fields as the OPD module:

### Acvilas AI Panel
The **Acvilas AI** panel appears at the top of the workspace, providing an AI-generated clinical summary for the loaded patient. Click to expand it for details or type a question in the Ask field.

### Items Table
Displays all services, products, and prescriptions added to this visit with columns for Item, Detail, Ref., Price, Discount, Total, and Option. Use **Make template** to save the current item set as a reusable template. Use **Clear All Items** to remove everything.

### Prescription Tab
Fill in the clinical consultation fields:

| Field | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Past Medical History** | Patient's known background conditions |
| **Presenting Complaint** | Reason for today's visit |
| **Allergies** | Known drug or other allergies |
| **Treatments** | Treatment plan for this visit |

Use the **Outside Prescription** table below to add medications with Drug Name, Qty, Dosage, Frequency, and Days, then click **Add**.

Use **Attachments** to upload files and **Print** to print the prescription.

### Services Tab
Add billable clinical services to the visit. Search by name, title, or code and click **Add** next to the relevant service.

### Templates Tab
Load a previously saved consultation template to auto-fill common service and prescription combinations.

### Products Tab
Dispense pharmacy products. Search by generic name, code, or product name and click **Add** to include items in the bill.

### Patient History Button
Click **Patient History** (top of the consultation area) to view the full historical record of this patient's previous visits and consultations.

---

## 4.5 Completing a Consultation from Appointment Management

Once the consultation is documented:

1. Click **Save** (orange) to save progress without closing the record.
2. Click **Mark Complete** (green, in the header bar) to finalize the consultation. This updates the appointment status to *Complete* and removes the patient from the Waiting List.

---

# Chapter 5: Customers

The **Customers** module is the central patient records database. It allows staff to search for any patient, view and edit their personal profile, and access their complete history of appointments, invoices, and medical reports — all in one place. Access it by clicking **Customers** in the left sidebar.

---

## 5.1 Customers Screen Overview

When you first open the Customers module, you will see a clean screen with a single **Search phone number** field in the top right corner. The system requires a phone number search to locate a patient record.

---

## 5.2 Searching for a Customer

1. Click the **Search phone number** field at the top right of the screen.
2. Type the patient's phone number (e.g., *763778282*).
3. The system will display all registered names linked to that phone number as clickable badges (e.g., *Mr. Layan*, *Mr. layan 5*).
4. Click the patient name badge you wish to open.

> **Note:** Multiple records can share the same phone number. Always verify the correct record by checking the name before opening.

---

## 5.3 Customer Profile Page

Once a patient is selected, their full profile page loads. This page is divided into four main sections.

---

### Section 1 — Personal Information

A numbered list of the patient's profile fields, each with an **Edit** button to update that specific field:

| # | Field | Description |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Name** | Patient's full name |
| 2 | **Phone** | Contact phone number |
| 3 | **Address** | Home or contact address |
| 4 | **ID Number** | National ID or other identification number |
| 5 | **Weight** | Patient's body weight |
| 6 | **Age** | Patient's age |
| 7 | **City** | City of residence |
| 8 | **Ethnicity** | Patient's ethnicity |
| 9 | **Sex** | Patient's gender |

At the bottom of this section, click **Print Barcode** to generate and print a barcode label for the patient's physical record or file.

To edit any field, click the **Edit** button next to it, make your changes, and save.

---

### Section 2 — Reports

On the right side of the profile (next to Personal Information), the **Reports** panel shows all medical/lab reports linked to this patient.

Each report row shows:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Service Name** | The type of service/test ordered (e.g., Abdominal Scan) |
| **Sub Div** | The subdivision or sub-category of the service |
| **Code** | The service billing code |
| **Ref. To** | Referral destination if applicable |
| **Ref. Name** | Name of the referring doctor or entity |
| **Status** | Current report status — **Pending** (orange) or **Completed** (green) |
| **Options** | Click **View** to open the full report details |

Click **Refresh** (next to the Reports heading) to reload and update the report list.

---

### Section 3 — Appointments

Below the personal information section, the full **Appointments history** table lists every appointment this patient has ever had:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **#** | Row number |
| **ID** | Appointment ID |
| **Doctor** | The doctor seen |
| **Customer** | Patient name |
| **Phone** | Patient phone |
| **Date** | Appointment date |
| **Time** | Appointment time |
| **Status** | Status badge (Waiting, Pending, Complete, etc.) |
| **Created** | Timestamp of when the appointment was created |
| **Payment** | Payment status badge (Paid / Not Paid) |
| **Details** | Click **View** to open the full appointment details popup |

Click **Refresh** (next to the Appointments heading) to reload the list.

---

### Section 4 — Invoice

At the bottom of the customer profile page, the full **Invoice history** table lists every billing transaction for this patient:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Invoice** | Invoice number |
| **C. Name** | Customer name |
| **C. Phone** | Customer phone |
| **Cashier** | The POS/cashier ID used (e.g., POS0001) |
| **Operator** | The staff member who processed the payment (e.g., ADMIN) |
| **Total** | Total amount billed |
| **Created at** | Date and time the invoice was generated |
| **Option** | Click **View** to open the full invoice |

---

## 5.4 Editing Customer Information

To update any detail in the patient's profile:

1. Locate the field you wish to change in the Personal Information section.
2. Click the **Edit** button on the right side of that row.
3. A text input will appear — enter the updated information.
4. Confirm/save the change.

> **Tip:** Keep patient records up to date, especially phone numbers, as the phone number is the primary search key used across OPD, Appointments, and Cashier modules.

---

## 5.5 Printing a Patient Barcode

At the bottom of the Personal Information section, click **Print Barcode** to print a barcode label for the patient. This barcode can be attached to physical files, prescriptions, or sample labels and scanned using the **ID Scan** feature in OPD or Appointment modules for fast record retrieval.

