---

## 12.2.5 Creating a New Role

Click **Create New Role** (top right) to open the **Create New WP Role** popup.

1. Enter the **Role Name** in the text field (e.g., *Receptionist*, *Lab Technician*, *Nurse*).
2. Click **Submit** (purple button) to create the role.
3. The new role will then appear in the **Select Role** dropdown.
4. You can then assign permissions to it as described in Section 12.2.4.

---

## 12.2.6 Permission Reference Guide

The table below describes the key permissions available in the system:

| Permission Name | What It Controls |
|---|---|
| **TV Projector Control** | Access to the TV Projector/queue display module |
| **View Customer Directory** | Access to view the Customers module |
| **System Report** | Access to the Reports module |
| **Task Tab 1 / 2 / 3** | Access to specific service task department tabs in Service Task module |
| **View POS Balance Sheet** | Access to view the cashier balance sheet |
| **Laboratory Administration** | Access to manage lab settings in Administration |
| **Service Control** | Access to manage services in Administration |
| **Doctor Control** | Access to manage doctor profiles in Administration |
| **User Control** | Access to manage user accounts in Administration |
| **Role Control** | Access to manage user roles in Administration |
| **Waiting List Control** | Access to manage and view the patient waiting list |
| **Promotion Control** | Access to manage promotions and discounts |

> **Best Practice:** Assign only the permissions each role genuinely needs. For example, a Cashier role should have billing and POS access but not Doctor Control or Administration settings. This protects sensitive data and reduces the risk of accidental changes.

