# Chapter 12.9: Administration — Bulk Actions

The **Bulk Actions** module allows administrators to perform mass system-wide operations on records across a selected date range. These are powerful tools designed to clean up or update large volumes of data in a single action. Access it from **Administration > Bulk Actions** (systemBulkAction).

---

## 12.9.1 Bulk Actions Screen Overview

The screen is titled **System Bulk Actions** and displays a critical warning at the top:

> ⚠️ **"This action will affect all system data. Once executed, the changes cannot be undone."**

This warning must be taken seriously. Bulk actions make permanent, irreversible changes to the database. Always double-check the date range and the action before clicking Execute.

---

## 12.9.2 Available Bulk Actions

### Waiting Appointments → Complete

This is the currently available bulk action. It mass-updates all appointments that are still in **Waiting** status within a specified date range, changing them all to **Complete** status in a single operation.

**When to use this:**
- At the end of a day or week when many appointments remain in "Waiting" status because staff forgot to manually mark them as complete
- During system cleanup or data reconciliation periods
- When closing out a past period and ensuring all appointment records are properly finalised

**How to execute:**

1. Set the **Start Date** (left date picker) — enter the beginning of the date range in YYYY-MM-DD format
2. Set the **End Date** (right date picker) — enter the end of the date range
3. Click the **Execute** button (purple, far right) to run the bulk action

The system will then update all appointments with a *Waiting* status that fall within the selected date range, changing them all to *Complete*.

---

## 12.9.3 Critical Warnings and Best Practices

> ⚠️ **This action cannot be undone.** Once you click Execute, all affected appointments are permanently marked as Complete. There is no undo or rollback option.

Before executing any bulk action, always:

- **Verify the date range carefully** — an incorrect date range could mark future or unintended appointments as complete
- **Run during off-peak hours** — execute bulk actions when the clinic is not actively seeing patients to avoid conflicts with live data
- **Confirm with your team** — ensure all relevant staff (doctors, receptionists) are aware the bulk action is being run, especially if it affects today's records
- **Export a report first** — before running a bulk action, download a CSV of the affected appointments from the **Appointment Report** (Reports module) so you have a record of what was in Waiting status before the change
- **Only Administrators should have access** to this module — ensure the Bulk Actions permission is restricted in User Roles

---

## 12.9.4 Why Bulk Actions Are Needed

In a busy clinic, it is common for some appointments to remain in *Waiting* status at the end of a day if the consultation was completed but the record was not manually closed. Over time, these accumulate and distort the Dashboard counters and Appointment Reports. The Bulk Actions tool provides a quick and controlled way to clean up these records across a defined historical period.

---

