## 12.10.5 Adding Parameters to a Report Template

From within the Lab Report Template builder, click **+ Add** in the left panel to open the **Add New Parameter** popup.

This popup shows the full list of all parameters from the global Result Parameters library:
- **WBC23** — LOINC: 7588 — unit: d/dL
- **WBC** — LOINC: 7188 — unit: d/dL
- **WBC2** — LOINC: 7188 — unit: d/dL2
- **Hemoglobin** — unit: g/dL

Use the **Search by name or LOINC code** field to find a specific parameter quickly.

To add a parameter:
1. Click on the parameter row to select it (it will highlight).
2. Click **+ Submit** (teal button, bottom right) to add it to the report template.
3. The parameter will appear in the left panel of the template builder.
4. You can then configure its reference ranges in the right panel.

Click **Cancel** to close without adding.

